@node "installation" "Installing PolyGraph      "
@prev "introduction"
@{bg shine}Installing PolyGraph could not be easier!@{bg back}

1. Unpack the archive called "PolyLab20.0.lha" to a drive (for
   example "Work:" or "DH0:").
   If you don't know how to do that, get the program "lha" first
   and read the documentation.
   To unpack you will probably give a command in the shell like:

   "@{fg shine}lha x DIR:PolyLab20.0.lha Work:@{fg text}"
   or
   "@{fg shine}lha x DIR:PolyLab20.0.lha DH0:@{fg text}"

   where "DIR:" indicates the path which contains "PolyLab20.0.lha".
   A drawer (or subdirectory) called "PolyInstall" will be created,
   which contains the whole distribution.

2. If the whole distribution (all files and directories) is in the
   new directory "PolyInstall" open that drawers window.

3. You will recognize two icons called "InstallPoly1.3" and
   "InstallPoly2.0". If you double-click on "InstallPoly1.3",
   PolyGraph will be installed on a system with Workbench 1.3.
   The destination drive will be "DH0:".
   Double-click on "InstallPoly2.0" if your Workbench version is
   higher or equal to 2.0. The destination drive will be "Work:",
   where two drawers "PolyGraph" and "PriDat" will be created.

4. If you do not want to install PolyGraph on the drives "DH0:"
   or "Work:", you should give the shell-commands
   "@{fg shine}cd SRC:PolyInstall@{fg text}"
   "@{fg shine}execute InstallPoly1.3 DEST:@{fg text}"
   or
   "@{fg shine}cd SRC:PolyInstall@{fg text}"
   "@{fg shine}execute InstallPoly2.0 DEST:@{fg text}"

   where "SRC:" is the drive which contains the drawer
   "PolyInstall", and "DEST:" is your destination drive.
   On "DEST:" the two drawers "PolyGraph" and "PriDat" will be
   created.

5. The install script copies the "reqtools.library" and the
   "polymath.library" to "LIBS:". A new Amiga-OS command "polymath"
   will be copied to "C:".

6. Depending on the Workbench version two assigns will be written
   into "StartupII" (1.3) or "user-startup" (2.0+) in "S:".

7. You should check if two new assigns "@{fg shine}PG:@{fg text}" and "@{fg shine}PriDat:@{fg text}" are there.

8. You can delete the drawer (or directory) "PolyInstall" if
   the installation was successful.
@endnode

@node "start_pg" "Starting PolyGraph V2.0.0"
@prev "installation"
@{bg shine}Starting PolyGraph V2.0.0:@{bg back}

There are two possible ways to start the main program PolyGraph:

1. Double-click on the icon "PolyGraph.V20.0".

2. Open a shell-window, change to the directory which contains
   the program (e.g. with "cd Work:PolyGraph") and enter
   "PolyGraph.V20.0" (or give the whole pathname in front).

The @{b}TOOLTYPES@{ub} (default values in brackets) are as follows:

   POINTS=#          Sets maximum number of datablocks to # (1024)

   DATAFILE=#        Name # of the file to load (PolyGraph.xy-1)

   CONFIGFILE=#      Name # of the configuration file for PolyMeas
                     (PolyGr.cfg)

   TOKENS=0-4        To choose symbols for points (0):
                     0 - plus signs
                     1 - crosses
                     2 - circles
                     3 - points
                     4 - small points

   X=#               Number of datafield for display of x-values (1)

   Y=#               Number of datafield for display of y-values (2)

   Z=#               Number of results field (0: no results)

   MWINDOW=#         Specification of console-window for I/O-operations
                     within @{"ARexx scripts" link "arexx_examples" 0} or for debugging purposes in
                     PolyMeas (CON:240/100/400/100/ARexx).

   XMIN=#            Starting value for X_Minimum (-1.0e+09).

   XMAX=#            Starting value for X_Maximum ( 5.0e+10).

   YMIN=#            Starting value for Y_Minimum (-1.0e+09).

   YMAX=#            Starting value for Y_Maximum ( 5.0e+10).

   MEASURE=0|1       Flag for autostarting PolyMeas (0: no autostart).

   WBSCREEN=0|1      If 1 chooses workbench screen for PolyGraph windows
                     (0: custom screen for PolyGraph).

   INTERLACE=0|1     If on custom screen chooses interlace mode on
                     PAL and NTSC monitors (0: no interlace).

   MONITOR=PAL|NTSC  Specification of monitor (PAL).

   OLDLOOK=0|1       If WB2.0+ shows old look: WB 1.3 colors (0).
                     Usable only on custom screen.

   OLDBUTTONS=0|1    If WB2.0+, lets the user choose the old 1.3 look
                     for buttons and text gadgets (0: use new look,
                     use gadtools.library).

   DIAGRAMCOLORS=0-3 Preset of the foreground/background colors of
                     the diagram in the PolyGraph main window
                     (0: black/white).

   PENCOLOR=0-7      Preset of color for fixed objects (default is
                     6 for OLDLOOK=1, or 7).

   WINDOWHEIGHT=#    Preset of height of main window (245).

   WINDOWWIDTH=#     Preset of width of main window (640).

   SUPERBITMAP=0|1   If 1 uses superbitmap window as main window.
                     There is no adjustment of the diagram to the
                     window dimensions.

   WINDOW=#          Specification of console-window for menu item
                     'Debug' of the main window (only for testing
                     and debugging purposes).


If you start PolyGraph from a shell you can also give command options: To see a
list of options type "PolyGraph.V20.0 -h" at the command prompt. The argument of
an option must be given without blanks, ie. just after the option.

If you want speak output, you should have the "narrator.device" in "DEVS:" and
the "translator.library" in "LIBS:".

While the program PolyGraph starts, it reads a file called
"PolyGraph.V20.0.pref", which contains all settings last used (the TOOLTYPE
settings are not affected). If you have not defined a data file to read in
(TOOLTYPE DATAFILE=#) and have not given any starting values for the diagram
borders, you are asked to type in the borders for the diagram first.
@endnode

@node "start_pm" "Starting PolyMeas V2.0.0"
@prev "start_pg"
@{bg shine}Starting PolyMeas V2.0.0:@{bg back}

To start the independent measurement process you can do the following:

1. Define the TOOLTYPE MEASURE=1 or the command option -PM when
   starting PolyGraph (PolyMeas will be started automatically).

2. Start PolyGraph and click the button 'Meas' near the bottom of the
   diagram.

3. Start PolyGraph and press the <TAB> key, if the PolyGraph main window
   is active.

PolyMeas can not be started separately, because it needs the communication with
PolyGraph. To stop PolyGraph, switch off PolyMeas first. If a start/
stop-measurement is active and running, it is not possible to stop PolyMeas.
Stop the start/stop-measurement first.

If you start several PolyGraph and PolyMeas processes, remember that the serial
port can only be used by one PolyMeas process (often the one which is started
first). Up to 4 IEEE-488 interface cards with different unit numbers are allowed
in one Amiga, so you may operate with 4 PolyMeas processes to communicate with
them.
@endnode

@node "print_diagrs" "Printing diagrams in PolyGraph V2.0.0        "
@prev "start_pm"
@{bg shine}Printing diagrams with PolyGraph V2.0.0:@{bg back}

It is really easy to print high quality diagrams with PolyGraph. There is a menu
item called "Actions/PriDat Diagram" you can use. The whole diagram area
consisting of the editable data, the legends and frozen objects will be sent to
PriDat.V20.0 to print a diagram in the background (with lower priority). You can
choose between 3 different printers with 5 resolutions. If you have a printer
which is not in the list, don't worry. PriDat.V20.0 can make an IFF-file which
can be printed on every printer using the Workbench printer drivers.

There are several options for printout:

1. You can force PriDat.V20.0 to show a preview of the printout, which
   will be an exact WYSIWYG of the diagram on the paper.

2. You can allow PriDat.V20.0 to print your diagram without check.

3. If you want to see the preview on the workbench, you can tell
   PriDat.V20.0 to do it.

4. You can force PriDat.V20.0 to generate an IFF-file with adjustable
   width and height, which can be printed with the Workbench printer
   drivers. Of course, this IFF-file can be manipulated with every
   paint program. The IFF-file has the same resolution as on the printer,
   so if you choose 300 dpi for printout, you get large files.

To set the option you want, you must edit the file "PriDat.V18.x" in the PriDat:
directory. Give the command line with the option you need and comment out the
rest. More information can be found in the @{"manual" link "manual" 0} for PolyGraph.

To get high quality diagrams using PriDat.V20.0 you should have a minimum of 2
MB free RAM when starting PolyGraph.V20.0.

Experienced users can also start PriDat.V20.0 alone to print out diagrams
showing measured data which have been stored to files. If you start PriDat.V20.0
in the shell, set the stack to at least 70000 bytes, otherwise the program will
guru.
@endnode

@node "arexx" "The ARexx Port of PolyGraph V2.0.0"
@prev "print_diagrs"
@{bg shine}The ARexx port of PolyGraph & PolyMeas V2.0.0:@{bg back}

PolyGraph's ARexx port offers all the functionality of the main diagram and main
measurement panel, and more besides.

The first @{b}portname@{ub} is "PolyMeas.Host", all next ports are called
"PolyMeas.Host_nn", where "nn" is a two digit number. If the second PolyMeas
process is meant, "nn" should be 01, for the third process "nn" = 02, and so
on.

It is not possible to control PolyGraph from ARexx without having started
PolyMeas, too. The ARexx software is built into PolyMeas and commands for
PolyGraph are sent to it over message ports. In this way it is possible to have
only one portname (no need to switch between two names) with the advantage of
having control over both programs PolyGraph & PolyMeas.

Here is an @{b}alphabetical list@{ub} of all the commands that PolyGraph & PolyMeas
support (arguments in [] are optional):

   'Abort'                             Send IFC-Signal on IEEE-488 bus.
   'AddDataPorts' PortNumbers          Define multiple PolyGraph processes for
                                       data visualization.
   'BaudRate' BaudRateValue            Sets the baudrate for serial-port I/O.
   'ChooseKey' FirstKey [SecondKey]    Simulates a key press in the diagram
                                       window (PolyGraph).
   'ChooseMenu' MenuItem [Info|Flag]   Simulates a menu choice in the diagram
                                       window (PolyGraph). See ARexx examples.
   'Clear' [DeviceNrs]                 Send SDC or DCL-commands over IEEE-488.
   'CloseIEEE'                         Closes the interface to IEEE-488.
   'ConfigWindow' MenuFlag             Opens/closes the configuration window
                                       of PolyMeas.
   'DataFile' [FileName]               Sets a new name for the datafile of the
                                       measurement window (PolyMeas).
   'DebugIO' MenuFlag                  Switches I/O-debugging on/off
                                       (menu item of PolyMeas).
   'Delay' DelayTime                   Sets the delay in 1/50 seconds
                                       (used in PolyMeas).
   'EOSMode' MenuFlag                  Switches End-Of-String mode on/off when
                                       reading data from IEEE-488.
   'FitFormula' Formula                Defines a formula for menu "Formula Fit"
                                       in PolyGraph.
   'GetCoeff' Index                    Reads a coefficient from the "Coeffi-
                                       cients"-window of PolyGraph into ARexx.
   'GetData' GraphIndex DataFieldNr    Reads data displayed in the diagram of
                                       PolyGraph into ARexx.
   'GetValue' DataFieldNr|'i'          Reads measured data from PolyMeas.
   'GiveInfo' InfoText                 Displays information in the titlebar of
                                       the PolyMeas-window (and optionally
                                       speaks it).
   'GoOn'                              Initiates next start/stop measurement
                                       cycle (PolyMeas).
   'GraphToBack'                       Puts diagram window behind.
   'GraphToFront'                      Puts diagram window in front of all
                                       other windows.
   'HighSpeedMode' MenuFlag            Sets High-Speed-Mode on IEEE-488 bus.
   'IEEEStatus'                        Reads status of 7210-controller.
   'IEEEUnit' [UnitNumber]             Specifies which IEEE-488 card will be
                                       used.
   'IOReqActual'                       Gives number of sent/recieved bytes.
   'IOReqStatus'                       Status of I/O-operation on IEEE-488.
   'Listen' DeviceNr                   Switches IEEE-488 Device into
                                       Listen mode.
   'LoadConfig' ConfigFile             Loads new measurement configuration
                                       from file into PolyMeas.
   'Local' [DeviceNrs]                 Sends GTL-command or disable REN-line.
   'MeasBlock'                         Simulates a single start/stop measure-
                                       ment cycle (PolyMeas).
   'MeasToBack'                        Puts measurement window behind all
                                       other windows.
   'MeasToFront'                       Puts measurement window in front of
                                       all other windows.
   'MeasureIEEE' DeviceNr Command      Sends Command to a certain Device and
                                       reads the response (PolyMeas).
   'MoveGraph' Left Top Width Height   Moves the diagram window to the
                                       specified position.
   'MoveMeas'  LeftEdge TopEdge        Moves the measurement window (PolyMeas)
                                       to the specified position.
   'MovePGScreen' TopEdge              Drags the screen for PolyGraph to a
                                       new position defined by TopEdge.
   'MultReadIEEE' DeviceNr Counter     Reads multiple data from a device and
                                       returns the mean value.
   'NewPolyPort' NameOfPort            Switches to another PolyGraph process's
                                       port to communicate with.
   'OldPolyPort'                       Switches back to the original port.
   'OpenIEEE'                          Open the interface to the IEEE-488 card.
   'PGScreenToBack'                    Puts the screen for PolyGraph behind
                                       all other screens.
   'PGScreenToFront'                   Puts the PolyGraph screen in front.
   'Plot' Xvalue Yvalue                Shows data pairs directly in the diagram
                                       of PolyGraph.
   'PollReadIEEE' DeviceNr BitNr       Conducts a serial poll and reads from
                                       a certain device if a certain bit is
                                       set (PolyMeas).
   'PPoll'                             Conducts a parallel poll on IEEE-488.
   'PPollConfig' ConfigString          Configures devices for parallel poll.
   'ReadIEEE' DeviceNrs                Reads data values from devices con-
                                       nected to IEEE-488.
   'ReadLnIEEE' DeviceNrs              Reads bytes with termination characters
                                       from IEEE-488 devices.
   'Remote'                            Sets the REN-line high on IEEE-488.
   'SaveConfig' ConfigFile 'OverWrite' Saves the measurement configuration to
                                       a certain file (PolyMeas).
   'SaveData'                          Saves all measured values from a
                                       start/stop-measurement in PolyMeas.
   'SendCoeff' Coeff Index             Sends a value to PolyGraph to be
                                       read as a fit or formula coefficient.
   'SendData' [GraphIndex]             Sends the whole block of measured data
                                       (PolyMeas) to PolyGraph for visuali-
                                       zation.
   'SendIEEE' DeviceNr Command         Sends the string Command to a device
                                       on the IEEE-488 bus.
   'SetGraphLimits' XMin XMax YMin YMx Sets new diagram limits in PolyGraph.
   'SetIndex' GraphIndex               Sets the actual index of displayed data.
   'SetSRQTask' NameOfTask SignalNr    Defines the task which will be signalled
                                       if a SRQ is detected on IEEE-488.
   'ShowData'                          Simulates the 'Show'-Button in the
                                       measurement window (PolyMeas).
   'SPoll' DeviceNrs                   Conducts a serial poll on the defined
                                       IEEE-488 devices (PolyMeas).
   'Start' Index ['Append']            Initiates a start/stop-measurement which
                                       has been configured previously in the
                                       measurement window (PolyMeas).
   'Stop'                              Stops a start/stop-measurement.
   'StopPoly'                          Stops both the PolyMeas and the Poly-
                                       Graph processes.
   'StoreValue' Value DataFieldNr      Stores values as measured data in
                                       a start/stop-measurement (PolyMeas).
   'Talk' DeviceNr                     Puts a certain device in Talk-mode.
   'TermChars' [CharNr1] [CharNr2]     Defines the termination characters for
                                       command strings (IEEE-488 and serial).
   'TimeOut' Time                      Sets the timeout value for readings
                                       from IEEE-488 or serial port.
   'Trigger' DeviceNrs                 Sends a GET-command on IEEE-488.
   'UnListen' DeviceNr                 Puts a certain device in Unlisten-mode.
   'UnTalk' DeviceNr                   Puts a certain device in Untalk-mode.
   'WBenchToBack'                      Workbench screen is brought behind all
                                       other screens.
   'WBenchToFront'                     Puts the Workbench screen in front of
                                       all other screens.


Using the ARexx port will allow you to interface PolyGraph with other scientific
programs, such as Maple® for the Amiga. For complex measurement problems you can
control PolyMeas & PolyGraph in the way you need. For more information please
look into the manual or see the examples.
@endnode

@node "arexx_examples" "ARexx example scripts     "
@prev "arexx"
@{bg shine}ARexx example scripts:@{bg back}

The example scripts are in the drawer Rexx (or after @{"installation" link "installation" 0} of PolyGraph
in the Rexx: directory). To use these scripts start @{"PolyGraph" link "start_pg" 0} and @{"PolyMeas" link "start_pm" 0},
choose the menu item 'ARexx/Execute Program...' and enter the name of the script
you want to test. The name should be given without extension (.rexx). Use only
the scripts called test#?.rexx. The GPIB/test#?.rexx scripts are for users of
IEEE-488.

   @{"test-00.rexx" link "test-00.rexx" 0}         Example for 'GiveInfo'
   @{"test-02.rexx" link "test-02.rexx" 0}         Example for 'Plot', 'ShowData'
   @{"test-03.rexx" link "test-03.rexx" 0}         Example for 'DataFile', 'StoreValue', 'SendData',
                                    'ShowData', 'SetIndex' and 'GetData'.
   @{"test-05.rexx" link "test-05.rexx" 0}         Example for 'TermChars', 'OpenIEEE', 'Remote',
                                    'MeasureIEEE', 'ReadIEEE', 'ReadLnIEEE',
                                    'SendIEEE', 'Plot', 'Local', 'CloseIEEE'.
   @{"test-30.rexx" link "test-30.rexx" 0}         Example for 'ChooseMenu Change Description'
   @{"test-31.rexx" link "test-31.rexx" 0}         Example for 'ChooseMenu Change X_Minimum',
                                    'ChooseMenu Change X_Maximum',
                                    'ChooseMenu Change Y_Minimum',
                                    'ChooseMenu Change Y_Maximum'
   @{"test-32.rexx" link "test-32.rexx" 0}         Example for 'ChooseMenu Load' and
                                    'ChooseMenu Save as'.
   @{"test-33.rexx" link "test-33.rexx" 0}         Example for 'ChooseMenu Use All Indices',
                                    'ChooseMenu Show Buttons',
                                    'ChooseMenu X-Value fixed',
                                    'ChooseMenu Y-Value fixed',
                                    'ChooseMenu Debug',
                                    'ChooseMenu Sort by X-Value',
                                    'GraphToFront', 'MeasToFront',
                                    'GraphToBack', 'MeasToBack',
                                    'WBenchToFront', 'PGScreenToBack',
                                    'ChooseKey DEL'.
   @{"test-34.rexx" link "test-34.rexx" 0}         Example for 'ChooseMenu PriDat Diagram NEC P6',
                                    'ChooseMenu Graphicdump Black/White',
                                    'ChooseMenu Graphicdump Colors',
                                    'ChooseMenu Change Pen Color'.
   @{"test-35.rexx" link "test-35.rexx" 0}         Example for 'MoveGraph', 'MoveMeas', 'MovePGScreen'.

   @{"test12.rexx" link "test12.rexx" 0}          Small measurement example (only for demonstration).
   @{"test15.rexx" link "test15.rexx" 0}          Measurement simulation example.
   @{"test16.rexx" link "test16.rexx" 0}          Tests the 'Fast Fourier Transformation' from ARexx.
   @{"test17.rexx" link "test17.rexx" 0}          Tests the menu item 'Derivation' from ARexx.
   @{"test18.rexx" link "test18.rexx" 0}          Tests the menu item 'Smoothing' under ARexx.
   @{"test19.rexx" link "test19.rexx" 0}          Tests the menu item 'Scaling' under ARexx.
   @{"test20.rexx" link "test20.rexx" 0}          Shows how to use the 'Polynomial Fit' from ARexx.

   @{"GPIB/test6.rexx" link "test6.rexx" 0}      Measures and plots 10 data pairs from IEEE-488
                        devices (DVM and scanner are used).
   @{"GPIB/test9.rexx" link "test9.rexx" 0}      Shows how to make a serial poll before reading from
                        the Fluke 8840A DVM controlled by ARexx.
   @{"GPIB/test10.rexx" link "test10.rexx" 0}     Shows a second way to conduct a serial poll on the
                        Fluke 8840A Digital Voltmeter.
@endnode

@node "manual" "Getting the manual V2.0.0        "
@next "how_to_contact"
@prev "distribution"
@{fg shadow}@{bg shine}How to get the 300 pages manual:@{fg text}@{bg back}

You should first pay the fee to get the @{"registered version" link "distribution" 0} of PolyGraph,
PolyMeas and PriDat V2.0.0. You will get a disk containing the whole manual in
TeX-source format and as a DVI-file, which can be displayed with ShowDVI and
printed out with DVIprint using PasTeX (or another TeX-implementation). If you
don't have PasTeX, don't worry, because the TeX-sources on disk can be displayed
with any texteditor.

The easiest way to get the printed manual is to print out the file
"@{"OrderForm.Man" link "orderform_man" 0}" which is in this distribution. Fill out the form and send it to
the @{"author" link "how_to_contact" 0} (that's me). The printed manual costs 50,- DM (or the same value in
other currencies) because printing is not cheep and it is a lot of work, too.
@endnode

